params.name: message
params.description: a human readable description of this error.

name: name
description: the type of this error.

name: message
description: human readable description of this error.

name: TransactionRetryNeeded
description: Thrown when a transaction should be retried, either because the user called 'retry' or because values are missing.

name: MutationNotAllowed
description: Thrown when a user attempts to modify a value without using the appropriate methods.

name: CapabilityDenied
description: Thrown when a user attempts to read or write with a reference that doesn't allow it.

name: TransactionRejectedError
description: Thrown when the server sends back an error because it was not able to commit the transaction.

name: src/gos-connection.js
GosConnection
description:
GosConnections represent the connection to the GoshawkDB.

They should be acquired through the static {@link Goshawk.connect} function.

name: clientInfo
description: The product and version information we sent to the server during the initial connection handshake.

name: serverInfo
description:
The product and version information we receive from the server during the initial handshake,
or null if it hasn't occurred yet.

name: namespace
description: The namespace that the server assigns to this client.

name: roots
description:
The roots that this client has access to.
Provided by the server during handshake.

name: connect
description:
Connects to the server.  If running in node, you will need to provide connectionOptions that include the client
certificate and key.

name: transact
description:
Queues a transaction for running, then ensures that transaction processing is happening.
The returned promise resolves with the value returned by the fn once the transaction has committed.  The fn may be
run multiple times and so should avoid side effects.
fn may be an asynchronous or a synchronous function.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<*, Error>} a promise that resolves to the result of the transaction function once the transaction submits or an error if it cannot.

params.name: fn
params.description: the transaction function.  This function may be run multiple times and should rethrow any TransactionRetryNeeded exceptions.

return.description: a promise that resolves to the result of the transaction function once the transaction submits or an error if it cannot.

name: close
description: Closes the underlying link.

params.name: response
params.description: the msgpack response.

params.name: clearCurrentTransaction
params.description: if true, this will first clear the current transaction.

name: src/goshawk.js
Goshawk
description: Goshawkdb client.

name: connect
description:
Connects to the websocket port of a goshawkdb server.
See the [goshawkdb documentation](https://goshawkdb.io/documentation.html) for more information.

params.name: url
params.description: the url of the websocket endpoint. e.g. wss://localhost:9999/ws

params.name: connectionOptions
params.description:
in node.js, the connection options are used to make the connection.
				They are for the WS module and are defined [here](https://github.com/websockets/ws/blob/master/doc/ws.md).
				The options should include `key`, `cert` and if you don't want it to check
				the server certificates, `{rejectUnauthorized: false}`.

return.description: A promise that resolves with a connection or rejects with an error.

name: src/msgpack-connection.js
MsgpackConnection
description: The websocket and Msgpack connection.

name: src/objectcache.js
ObjectCache
description: The top level object cache. It keeps objects value and refs stored against their id.

name: src/ref.js
Ref
description:
A Ref represents a pointer to an object in the database.
Each Ref also carries with it some capabilities that determine
which of the actions `read` and `write` can be done with that reference.

You can get a Ref either by looking at the roots of the transaction,
creating a new object or reading it from an objects references with
{@link Transaction#read}.

name: varId
description: The goshawkdb id of the object this reference refers to.

name: read
description: Whether this reference can be used to read the object.

name: write
description: Whether this reference can be used to write the object.

name: sameReferent
description:
Checks to see if this reference and the other reference
refer to the same object in the database.

unknown.tagValue: {boolean} true if the other reference points to the same object, false otherwise.

return.description: true if the other reference points to the same object, false otherwise.

unknown.tagValue: {Ref} a new reference the same as this one, but that cannot be used to read.

return.description: a new reference the same as this one, but that cannot be used to read.

unknown.tagValue: {Ref} a new reference the same as this one, but that cannot be used to write.

return.description: a new reference the same as this one, but that cannot be used to write.

unknown.tagValue: {string} a representation of this reference.  String representations are for debug only and are not considered part of the public API.

return.description: a representation of this reference.  String representations are for debug only and are not considered part of the public API.

name: src/transaction.js
Transaction
description:
A transaction represents an attempt to make a modification to the database.

The code associated with it may be required to run multiple times before it
successfully completes.  Care must be taken to make sure this will not
break the client environment.

Transactions are acquired by calling {@link Connection#transact}.

name: roots
description: The roots that this client has access to.

name: read
description: Reads the value and references from an object pointed to by a Ref.

params.name: ref
params.description: a reference to the object to read from.

throws.description: if ref does not have read capability.
if the object is not in cache. Do not catch this without rethrowing it.

name: write
description: Changes the value an dreferences of an object pointed to by a Ref.

params.name: ref
params.description: a reference to the object to be written.

params.name: value
params.description: the new value to be stored in the object.

params.name: refs
params.description: the references from this object to other objects.

name: create
description: Creates a new object and returns the reference to it.

unknown.tagValue: {Ref} a reference to the newly created object.

params.name: value
params.description: the value that the new object will be created with.

params.name: refs
params.description: the references that the new object will be created with.  This will default to the empty array.

return.description: a reference to the newly created object.

name: retry
description:
Stops the current transaction, and waits for any of the values that have been
read to change before rerunning.  No further transactions will be processed while
a transaction is waiting.

Internally, this method throws a TransactionRetryNeeded error.  If you catch it
and do not rethrow it, you will stop the retry behaviour from working.

name: transact
description:
Runs a nested transaction inside this transaction.

If a nested transaction fails, its modifications will not be seen by the parent transaction.

unknown.tagValue: {Promise<*, Error>} a promise that resolves to the result of the transaction function once the transaction submits or an error if it cannot.

params.name: fn
params.description: the transaction function.  This function may be run multiple times and should rethrow any TransactionRetryNeeded exceptions.

return.description: a promise that resolves to the result of the transaction function once the transaction submits or an error if it cannot.

name: src/uint64.js
Uint64
description: A representation of a Uint64, since otherwise javascript can't do them.

name: constructor
description: Makes a new Uint64 from a Uint8Array

params.name: uintArray
params.description: an array of bytes to be used to represent this 64 bit integer.

name: buffer
description: An arraybuffer representation of this value.

name: from
description: Creates a Uint64 from bytes

name: fromBinary
description: Creates a Uint64 from the first 8 bytes of one of the binary forms.

name: fromArrayBuffer
description:
Creates a Uint64 from an array buffer. Potentially with a byte offset.
Only the first 8 bytes will be taken.

params.name: byteOffset
params.description: the starting position in the array buffer. Defaults to 0.

name: inc
description:
Modifies this Uint64 to represent the succeeding integer.  If
this represents the largest integer the Uint64 can represent, it will wrap to 0.

name: set
description: Set the last last bytes.length bytes.

params.name: bytes
params.description: the bytes to set.

name: concat
description:
Returns an array buffer where this Uint64 is the first 8 bytes and
the passed buffer is the subsequent bytes.

params.name: buffer
params.description: the subsequent bytes.

name: toString
description:
A string representation of this Uint64.  This string representation is for debugging purposes
and does not form part of the public API.

name: src/utils.js

unknown.tagValue: {string} a hexadecimal representation of this binary.

params.name: binary
params.description: the binary we want to represent in hex.

return.description: a hexadecimal representation of this binary.

name: toArrayBuffer
description: Tries to convert a binary value into an array buffer.

params.name: value
params.description: the value to convert.

name: asPromise
description:
Runs the provided function, and wraps the output or thrown error in a promise.
This is useful for writing code that deals with functions that may be either synchronous or
asynchronous.

params.name: fn
params.description: the function that will be evaluated to populate the promise.
